Defendant Gary S Speagle in court with attorney Thomas Patrick Grieve.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to all counts of the Amended Information.  Court finds the defendant guilty.   The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

As to Counts 1 through 4:

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 12 days as to Count 1 only)
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;
Concurrent with each other but consecutive to any other sentences.

TERM OF PROBATION:  6 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s; 
*No Use or Possession of controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Attend Criminal Thinking course;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed;

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 as to Counts 1-4  (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 as to Counts 1-4  (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 60 days with Huber as to Counts 1-4 consecutive.  

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

AS TO COUNT 5:

60 DAYS HUBER consecutive with Huber for work and school; 

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
Defendant to report to Huber no later than 7:00 pm on September 8, 2016.

Court denies future expungement.  

Probation/jail sentence can be transferred to Milwaukee County with NO electronic monitoring.
